You're absolutely right! The leader key bindings need to go in your `settings.json` file, not `keybindings.json`. The `keybindings.json` file doesn't support Vim-style leader keys.

Here's what you need to add to your `settings.json` in the `vim.normalModeKeyBindingsNonRecursive` array:

```json
// Add these to your existing vim.normalModeKeyBindingsNonRecursive array in settings.json:

// DEBUG BINDINGS
{
  "before": ["<leader>", "d", "s"],
  "commands": ["workbench.action.debug.start"]
},
{
  "before": ["<leader>", "d", "c"],
  "commands": ["workbench.action.debug.continue"]
},
{
  "before": ["<leader>", "d", "p"],
  "commands": ["workbench.action.debug.pause"]
},
{
  "before": ["<leader>", "d", "r"],
  "commands": ["workbench.action.debug.restart"]
},
{
  "before": ["<leader>", "d", "q"],
  "commands": ["workbench.action.debug.stop"]
},

// Step debugging
{
  "before": ["<leader>", "d", "o"],
  "commands": ["workbench.action.debug.stepOver"]
},
{
  "before": ["<leader>", "d", "i"],
  "commands": ["workbench.action.debug.stepInto"]
},
{
  "before": ["<leader>", "d", "O"],
  "commands": ["workbench.action.debug.stepOut"]
},

// Breakpoints
{
  "before": ["<leader>", "d", "b"],
  "commands": ["editor.debug.action.toggleBreakpoint"]
},
{
  "before": ["<leader>", "d", "B"],
  "commands": ["editor.debug.action.conditionalBreakpoint"]
},
{
  "before": ["<leader>", "d", "l"],
  "commands": ["editor.debug.action.toggleLogpoint"]
},

// Debug UI
{
  "before": ["<leader>", "d", "v"],
  "commands": ["workbench.debug.action.focusVariablesView"]
},
{
  "before": ["<leader>", "d", "w"],
  "commands": ["workbench.debug.action.focusWatchView"]
},
{
  "before": ["<leader>", "d", "k"],
  "commands": ["workbench.debug.action.focusCallStackView"]
},
{
  "before": ["<leader>", "d", "h"],
  "commands": ["editor.debug.action.showDebugHover"]
}
```

Your `keybindings.json` stays as-is (what you originally shared) since it only handles non-Vim keybindings. The Vim leader commands must go in `settings.json` under the Vim configuration section.

So to clarify:
- **`keybindings.json`** = Regular VS Code keybindings (Cmd/Ctrl shortcuts)
- **`settings.json`** → `vim.normalModeKeyBindingsNonRecursive` = Vim-style bindings with leader key

